      • value

        public abstract java.lang.String value
        The name of the parameter

        This text is displayed when the user calls DESCRIBE FUNCTION ....

        If your Java class is compiled with the -parameters compiler flag, then name of the parameter will be inferred from the method declaration and this value can be left at the default. If compiling with out the -parameters compiler flag, use this property to provide the user with the name of the parameter.

        Returns:
        parameter name.

        ""

      • schema

        public abstract java.lang.String schema
        The schema for this parameter.

        For simple parameters, this is optional and can be determined from the Java value itself. For complex return types (e.g. Struct types), this is required and will fail if not supplied.

        Default:
        ""
